   <category name='food'>

      <section name='absinthe'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy absinthe - Cafe Blanc 1355'>
         A waitdroid pours you a very small glass of the highly potent drink. You knock it back in one - tears spring to your eyes and your brain feels like it's going to dribble out of your ears. All you can manage to say for the next few minutes is a strangled, croaked out, "Wow!"
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         A waitdroid gives a gallic shrug and sneers at you as you try to get a drink without paying.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='blanc'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Cafe Blanc - 1355'>
         You signal to one of the gallic waitdroids, and after not too long a delay, it brings you a croque monsieur - the French version of a toasted ham and cheese sandwich. The melted cheese oozes out the sides as you bite into it, making a dreadful mess, but the taste is so good it's worth it.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         The waitdroids have that kind of sixth sense which tells them when a potential customer hasn't got any money, so they ignore you.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='camile'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Brasserie - 1417'>
         The waitdroid puts a plate in front of you containing the house speciality: steak frite. The steak is a thin cut called "onglet" which has been grilled to perfection, so the inside is still almost raw and the outside seared to seal in the flavor. The French fries are long and thin, crisp and golden on the outside and fluffy inside. The pepper sauce is both creamy and piquant.
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         The green salad is fresh and crunchy, and coated with a delicious French dressing. You cannot remember when you last had a meal so wonderful.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='No money'>
         Without groats, all you can do is sniff the aromas coming from the kitchen. What a sad state to find yourself in!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='caviar'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - M/M Champers Bar 777'>
         Your 10 groats gets you the tiniest morsel of caviar, barely enough to fill the petite mother-of-pearl spoon upon which it is presented. It tastes marvelous but is gone in an instant, at which point the waitdroid takes the valuable spoon away from you, lest you were tempted to slip it into your pocket.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         If you don't have any money, you are certainly in the wrong place! Neither Minnie nor Maxie will serve paupers.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='champers'>

         <para number='1' comment='Sell champers - loc 777'>
         Maxie himself comes over and serves you, carefully removing the cork from a bottle of champagne without causing it to shoot across the room. He pours you a glass and goes back to the bar. You drink down the bubbly, pour yourself another glass, drink that... and pretty soon the bottle is empty. It is only then that you notice the bill: you've been charged 100 groats for the champers!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No funds for champers'>
         Minnie himself appears by your side and discreetly whispers to you that a credit check has shown you don't have enough money to buy a bottle of champagne. You ask just how much it costs, and are aghast to hear that they charge 100 groats a bottle!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='chaud'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Club Chaud - 1419'>
         A waitdroid fights through the crowds and shoves a long baguette into your hands. It has been split, spread with a very runny camembert cheese, then sandwiched back together again. The bread is still warm from the oven - it couldn't get much fresher - and the cheese is extremely ripe, and very smelly. A perfect French snack, in fact!
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         A waitdroid fights through the crowds to see what you want, but when you discover that you don't have enough groats to buy any food, it vanishes again.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='hotel'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Hotel Francois 1545'>
         You are served with a French continental breakfast - called "cafe complete" - an enormous cup of coffee, more like a soup bowl than a cup, with a freshly-baked croissant and a pot of peach jam to spread on it. Eating the croissant, you spray buttery crumbs everywhere, but a tiny cleaning droid zooms around sucking them up almost before they can hit the ground.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         If you are not a guest in the hotel, you have to pay for breakfast.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='observe'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Observation - 1994'>
         A towering club sandwich is placed before you: multiple layers of toasted white bread, containing turkey, bacon, lettuce, tomato and smooth white mayonnaise. The whole thing is held together with a long cocktail stick. You can hardly get your mouth round the sandwich to bite through it...
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         Finally you succeed in eating the whole thing without actually demolishing the layers in the process, and are left with the cocktail stick, which you slip into your pocket.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='No money'>
         You can't afford to eat here, so just relax and enjoy the view.
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='society'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food - Magsoc Members 521'>
         A standard ration pack is placed before you. This is the food explorers take with them when heading off to parts unknown, but since the link closed and exploration stopped, a big stockpile has built up, which society members are slowly eating their way through. The ratpack contains all the nutrients you need, but unfortunately has the taste and texture of cardboard. Still, you munch through it heroically, doing your duty to the society.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         The Society has never fed its members for free!
         </para>

      </section>

      <section name='spin'>

         <para number='1' comment='Buy food -Spinning wheel - 1035'>
         The barman hands you a plate containing an assortment of nibbles, including a small cheese and onion tartlet, a mini sausage roll, a hunk of cheese and a lump of pineapple on a stick, a chicken drumstick (well you assume it's chicken...) and some raw vegetables with a cheesy dip. It is all designed to be eaten with the minimum of fuss, and you munch your way through it without really noticing.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='No money'>
         Your attempt to get food without paying for it attracts a scowl from the owner, and he does not look like a person you want to offend.
         </para>

      </section>

