   <category name='newbod'>

      <section name='president'>

         <para number='1' comment='newbod puzzle complete [1]'>
         The president comes out from behind his desk to greet you. "Congratulations on successfully completing the test," he tells you. "I was monitoring it from up here and it was an excellent result. I have already registered your membership in the Society."
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='newbod puzzle complete [2]'>
         "I would also like to take the opportunity to thank you for your help in getting Victor out of the problems he was having with Starport Security. I took the liberty of transferring sufficient funds into your account to cover those expenses.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='newbod puzzle complete [3]'>
         "It is the custom of the Society to welcome new members with a few small gifts. First is the sum of 2,500ig to help defray the fuel costs involved in completing the test and the second is a voucher for ten days' worth of free exemption from customs.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='newbod puzzle complete [4]'>
         "If you show it to the customs manager in the starport, he will either give you a ten day certificate, or if you already have one, extend your current certificate by ten days. Use it as soon as possible, since it only has a limited life.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='newbod puzzle complete [5]'>
         "Finally, there is a special bonus for commanders and captains - by arrangement with Armstrong Cuthbert, an award of 50 hauler points, since the exploration you did for the test will help with Akaturi jobs when the time comes."
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='newbod puzzle complete [6]'>
         He smiles and shakes your hand. "So welcome to the Magellan Society. I hope our association will be fruitful, and I look forward to hearing more about your exploration in the future." With that he turns to talk to another explorer who has been waiting, more or less patiently, for the President to finish talking to you.
         </para>

      </section>

