      <section name='blythe'>

         <para number='1' comment='kiss blythe'>
         For a moment, your lips press against Blythe's perfectly proportioned, pleasingly pink, plump lips, but then it squirms away from you with a faint expression of distaste on its face. "I am sorry, but that's not one of the services I am prepared to offer," it says. "I have neither the interest, the skill, nor indeed the plumbing. Find someone else to indulge your baser urges."
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='Blythe chat - hello boys'>
         Blythe inclines his head politely. "Greetings, Mr %s," it says. "Welcome to Rotary Offices, supplier of services for the businessman. If you would tell me of your requirements, I will do my best to fulfil your needs."
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='hello girls'>
         Blythe inclines his head politely. "Greetings, Ms %s," it says. "Welcome to Rotary Offices, supplier of services for the businessman. If you would tell me of your requirements, I will do my best to fulfil your needs."
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='hello things'>
         Blythe inclines his head politely. "Greetings, M %s," it says. "Welcome to Rotary Offices, supplier of services for the businessman. If you would tell me of your requirements, I will do my best to fulfil your needs."
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='blythe/who'>
         It gives a small smile. "Blythe is all the name I have, and all I need. Who I am is not as important as my function, which is to act as the facilitator for all Rotary Offices customers. If you need to rent office space, or obtain secretarial or clerical services, or if your needs are more... shall we say... esoteric, I am certain that we can be of assistance."
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='rotary/where'>
         "Rotary Offices has been catering to the business community that visits Magellan since the space station's inauguration," Blythe explains. "Many companies do business here without having a permanent presence, and we rent them office space and hire them the staff they need, as well as providing just about anything else they require, no matter how specialist or odd."
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='office space/offices'>
         "We have a range of rooms from small cubbies up to grand suites, which can be used for meetings or as offices. They can be hired for a period as short as an hour or as long as you like..." Blythe starts to list the charges but since you have no need for office space, you don't pay much attention.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='secretarial/clerical/services'>
         "Our staff are available to contract on an hourly rate or, if your needs are more long-term, we can negotiate monthly or even yearly rates," Blythe tells you. "We have available people with all manner of skills, from secretarial and clerical to more... um... executive functions."
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='esoteric/specialist/odd/executi'>
         Blythe lowers its voice a little. "Since we are off Earth, the Galactic Administration's rules and regulations are not so strictly enforced as they are downstairs. This allows us to provide services which may not be freely available elsewhere. If you give me some idea of the kind of thing you are looking for, perhaps I can give you more information."
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='espionage/spying'>
         "I am afraid that's a little out of our line of work. Besides, the SpyNet organization pretty much has the private espionage business in Sol sewn up, so you should see about contacting them. They have an office in Earth's commercial area, I believe."
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='spynet'>
         "Nobody knows much about SpyNet; they are extraordinarily secretive. I suppose as spies that makes sense. Rotary Offices does not try to compete with SpyNet - we have our own areas of expertise." Blythe looks pensive for a moment. "As a young being I did cherish dreams of becoming some kind of intelligence agent, but it became clear my aptitudes did not incline in that direction."
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='sex'>
         Blythe laughs. "Oh dear, if that's what you are interested in, there are scores of kindly persons just waiting to relieve you of your groats in return for a moment of comfort - you don't need Rotary Offices for that. I, myself, do not indulge in the pleasures of the flesh. I cannot imagine what anyone sees in them."
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='magellan'>
         "I very much enjoy living and working on the space station," Blythe says. "There's a free and easy attitude here; you can do what you want and be who you want to be, and so long as you don't do anything that's bad for business, nobody cares. Anything goes, really, particularly anything that serves to part visitors from their money. That suits me."
         </para>

         <para number='14' comment='earth'>
         Blythe frowns. "I was born downstairs, and had a miserable childhood. I vowed to escape the planet as soon as I was old enough, by any means necessary. Oh, it's not that I have anything against Earth, not really, it's just that I detest the way the GA's rules and regulations bind so very tight. Things are much looser here."
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='ga/galactic administration'>
         Blythe's face takes on a somewhat pained expression. "I do detest the way bureaucracies end up perpetuating their own power. I've studied history, and although I admit the GA is not as bad as some, its sheer size and scale means its nature is always going to be oppressive to anyone who doesn't fit one of the clearly defined roles.
         </para>

         <para number='16'>
         "I turned out to be a very square peg that definitely did not fit into the round hole, and spent most of my childhood resisting being hammered into place. I did not want to fit, you see, and the institution which was charged with my care and comfort knew no way to deal with nonconformists like myself other than to use brute force - for my own good, of course."
         </para>

         <para number='17' comment='stat'>
         Blythe turns his head from side to side quickly, as if checking that nobody can overhear him. "Yes, recent developments have made it possible for various organizations to enhance the physical or mental capabilities of just about any type of being. Here, we have a service specializing in boosting endurance, or stamina as it is sometimes called.
         </para>

         <para number='18'>
         "It's all highly illegal, you understand. For all my talk about the GA's rules not applying here, they would come down on us hard if they had proof of just what service we are providing here. For the other stats, you will have to look elsewhere."
         </para>

         <para number='19' comment='stamina'>
         "We can increase your stamina but it's not a pleasant process for you, nor is it cheap. It's completely reliable, though - it works every time, I assure you.
         </para>

         <para number='20'>
         "So, to the details: 1 slithy will gain you 1 stamina point. But you can only do it once each day; your body won't take any more than that. In fact, that limit applies to all of the stat-boosting services you might avail yourself of - the most you can safely increase your attributes is one enhancement, of any of the stats, a day.
         </para>

         <para number='21'>
         "If you wish to improve your endurance, then BUY STAMINA."
         </para>

         <para number='22' comment='nomatch'>
         "I am so very sorry, that is not a service that we can offer at this time," says Blythe with an apologetic air.
         </para>

