   <category name='snark'>

      <section name='bellman'>

         <para number='1' comment='talk -assignment I'>
         Von Bellman puts down his knife and fork and looks directly at you for a long moment before replying. "The Directorate of Naval Intelligence, also known as the DNI, has asked the Magellan Society to find someone to act as their agent in an extremely sensitive assignment.
         </para>

         <para number='2' comment='talk - assignment II'>
         "It seems that the Snark asteroid has vanished. It was left in a remote section of the asteroid belt after its Hilbert Space generator was destroyed by DNI agents shortly after Ming vanished. It's no longer there and no one knows what has happened to it.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='talk - assignment III'>
         "The DNI want it back. Or at least they want it back in its orbit in the asteroid belt. And to do so they can't use a regular agent because of the extremely sensitive nature of the task. Indeed, I cannot emphasise enough how sensitive this is."
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='talk - assignment IV'>
         He picks up his fork, pauses, and then repeats the word, "Sensitive!", stabbing the fork in your direction for emphasis, after which he resumes eating his meal.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='talk - sensitive I'>
         He looks at you in surprise. "Of course it's sensitive. The whole of known space understands that the paradigm shift which caused the Interregnum was initmately bound up with the shenanigans around Snark.
         </para>

         <para number='7' comment='talk - sensitive II'>
         "That cut us off from the out-system planets for hundreds of years. If this gets out there will be mass panic that it might happen again. Hundreds of looneys will start 'investigating', muddying the trail and destroying valuable evidence.
         </para>

         <para number='8' comment='talk - sensative III'>
         "The DNI must get this matter dealt with before word leaks out, which is why they have asked the Society to recommend a suitable entity willing to act as their agent. If you are prepared to be that agent, just tell me that you accept."
         </para>

         <para number='10' comment='talk - accept I'>
         He smiles for the first time. "Excellent! Now... I know you are the one for the job, because we investigated you intensively before we picked you. However, the DNI insisted that you pass a test first. Basically you need to find their Sol System Border Field Office.
         </para>

         <para number='11' comment='talk - accept II'>
         "I have no idea where it is, so I can't give you any clues, although I suspect that the name of the office is indicative of its location. The DNI's assumption is that if you can't find their office, you are unlikely to be able to solve their problem!
         </para>

         <para number='12' comment='talk - accept III'>
         "And that reminds me, you will need this to prove your bona fides when you do find the entrance. Show it to whoever is in the room, and they will give you access to the field office. Be careful who you give it to. Giving it to the wrong person might be dangerous, or expensive..."
         </para>

         <para number='13' comment='talk - accept IV'>
         With that von Bellman hands you what appears to be a schedule for the production of some sort of heavy bulk processing machinery.
         </para>

         <para number='15' comment='talk dni/naval intel'>
         "I know only what is common public knowledge about the Directorate.", says von Bellman blandly. He clearly knows more than that. Probably a great deal more. Equally clearly, he isn't going to tell you anything else. "You really need to find them yourself if you want to gather any more information."
         </para>

         <para number='20' comment='talk - bye I'>
         Conversation drifts on to other topics unrelated to Snark, and the two of you finish a very pleasant meal washed down with an excellent bottle of green Mouton Rigelchild '53.
         </para>

         <para number='21' comment='talk - bye II'>
         Shaking hands you take your leave of von Bellman, and you hear him mutter, "I know you can do it." He repeats it a little louder, looks you straight in the eye and repeats his statement a third time. Finally, he warns you that as a security precaution he will, in the future, act as though he doesn't know you.
         </para>

         <para number='35' comment='talk - nomatch'>
         He shrugs and continues eating.
         </para>

