   <category name='stats'>

      <section name='stamina'>

         <para number='1' comment='buy stamina - no slithy'>
         Blythe ushers you through a door into a room that looks like a cross between a laboratory and a gymnasium. Before it hands you over to the technicians who will perform the procedure, it explains that it needs to know that you have the wherewithal to pay for it, and to that end you should display the certificate of slithy ownership. It is at this point you realize that you don't, in fact, have any slithies.
         </para>

         <para number='2'>
         With an embarrassed apology for wasting Blythe's time, you leave the room.
         </para>

         <para number='3' comment='basic message'>
         Blythe ushers you through a door into a room that looks like a cross between a laboratory and a gymnasium, and hands you over to the tender mercies of the technicians. They efficiently strip your clothing and proceed to give you a thorough check-up.
         </para>

         <para number='4' comment='already done a stat today'>
         After a moment, one of them frowns at you. "Didn't anyone explain how dangerous all this is? You've already had one of your personal attributes enhanced today, and your body just can't take the strain of any more treatment. Come back tomorrow." He ushers you back out of the lab/gym.
         </para>

         <para number='5' comment='stam is already maxed'>
         After a moment, one of the technicians looks at you in consternation. "Sorry, pal, you have already boosted your stamina as high as it will go; any further enhancement would risk catastrophic organ failure, and we're not prepared to risk it. It's more than my job's worth. Too big a liability, you know." He ushers you back out of the lab/gym.
         </para>

         <para number='6' comment='Increase stam'>
         Evidently, you pass, because they attach wires to various parts of your body and push you into a giant treadmill that looks like a hamster's wheel. It starts to rotate and you have no choice but to move with it, unless you want to be dumped onto the floor. It picks up speed and you are forced to run, fast, faster and then even faster, reaching what you assume is the height of your endurance.
         </para>

         <para number='7'>
         Just as you think you cannot keep going any longer, you feel sharp pains all over your body as a surge of power is sent over the wires to provide an extra stimulus.
         </para>

         <para number='8'>
         Finally, your ordeal comes to an end, but you actually feel fitter than you did before. The technicians give you another check, and pronounce themselves satisfied. One of them takes a certificate of slithy tove ownership from you, and ushers you back out of the lab/gym.
         </para>

         <para number='9' comment='Coda if player is now maxed'>
         Just before he says goodbye, he cautions you that you have increased your endurance to as great a level as is possible, so you should not risk trying to make your stamina any higher.
         </para>

      </section>

